reviewText: This is a rambling strange series of stories all involving the same people but puzzled together in a jigsaw helter skelter way without any timeline.  In other words it keeps jumping back and forth in time, making no discernible whole!  Ergo logic remains distant as the separate pieces float in and out of focus.  I must admit this seemed like a film school project that was rushed into final production to get a product out the door~

reviewText: This movie is incredibly disjointed and didn't make a bit of sense.  I was so confused through the whole thing.  It synopsis says the movie is about a crime scene photographer, but the one crime scene photographer in the film wasn't even a main character.  And the ending made no sense.  Idk.  I don't see how this was based on true events.

reviewText: This is not a movie.  I have no idea what to call it but it was not a movie. I'm really surprised there were folks who rated this so high.  Must be amigos of the clan who created this mess.  Half an hour into this parade  my dogs were closing their eyes and they never sleep during flick night.  BUMMER-RAMA score here.  I hope the next flick this producer kicks out is better than this boring story line.

reviewText: I don't mind low budget films, but this one was not worth my viewing time, even as a background flick. I watched it through hoping the conclusion would make sense of all the delusional flashbacks and the nutcase wife, but nope, it just left me befuddled and filled with regret that I bothered giving it a chance.
summary: Ultimately a confusing low budget mess
